] and transfer to the Strike Experimentation Group in 2019)<ref name=\"Dec162\">{{cite web|url=http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-statement/Commons/2016-12-15/HCWS367/|title=Strategic Defence and Security Review \u2013 Army: Written statement \u2013 HCWS367|publisher=Hansard|accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref>\n** 3rd Battalion, [[The Rifles]], in [[Redford Barracks|Edinburgh]]<ref name=\"rgbw-association2\">[http://www.rgbw-association.org.uk/newsletter2013.pdf The Rifles and The Royal Gloucestershire,Berkshire and Wiltshire Regiment Newsletter 2013]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130727183131/http://www.rgbw-association.org.uk/newsletter2013.pdf|date=July 27, 2013}} {{dead link|date=July 2013}}</ref> (to be equipped with [[Mechanised Infantry Vehicle]] and move to Catterick in 2021)\n\n==== 1st Artillery Brigade ====\n* '''[[1st Artillery Brigade (United Kingdom)|1st Artillery Brigade]]''', in [[Tidworth Camp|Tidworth]]<ref name=\"HQSouthWest\" />\n** [[National Reserve Headquarters, Royal Artillery]], controlling the specialist artillery batteries and watchkeeper pool.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bootcampmilitaryfitnessinstitute.com/2018/11/13/what-is-the-national-reserve-headquarters-royal-artillery-nrhq-ra/|title=What is the National Reserve Headquarters Royal Artillery (NRHQ RA)?|last=Andrew Marshall|date=2018-11-13|website=Boot Camp & Military Fitness Institute|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-11-03}}</ref>\n** Supporting the armoured infantry brigades:\n*** [[1st Regiment Royal Horse Artillery]], in [[Assaye Barracks|Tidworth]] <ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2017-03-21/68813/|title=Royal Artillery:Written question - 68813|website=UK Parliament|language=English|access-date=2019-11-03}}</ref>\n*** [[19 Regiment Royal Artillery|19th Regiment Royal Artillery]], in [[Bhurtpore Barracks|Tidworth]] <ref name=\":1\" />\n*** [[104 Regiment Royal Artillery|104th (Wales and Western) Regiment Royal Artillery]], in [[Newport, Wales|Newport]] <ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\"mead\">{{cite web|url=https://3.bp.blogspot.com/-xEUsn7hxDMo/WFMZfObk8EI/AAAAAAAAEho/2hLXO0xUOVUYorc22jED3FsIzvghnhEVgCLcB/s1600/Czv9xzCWIAE-W1B.jpg|title=Letter from Brigadier Mead|publisher=1st Artillery Brigade and Headquarters South West|accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"mead2\">{{cite web|url=https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/15492571_1338253552859669_4065325510072663045_n.jpg?oh=aec9617d2b8b8b163d0421a7f28ed84b&oe=58F15783 |title=Letter from Brigadier Mead Part 2 |publisher=1st Artillery Brigade and Headquarters South West |accessdate=19 December 2016 }}{{dead link|date=June 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n*** [[105 Regiment Royal Artillery|105th (Scottish and Ulster) Regiment Royal Artillery]], in [[Edinburgh]] <ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\"writtenanswer\">{{cite web|url=http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2017-03-21/68813/|title=Royal Artillery:Written question \u2013 68813 |publisher=Hansard|accessdate=5 April 2017}}</ref>\n** Supporting the strike brigades:\n*** [[3rd Regiment Royal Horse Artillery]], in [[Albemarle Barracks, England|Albemarle]] <ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\"mead\">{{cite web|url=https://3.bp.blogspot.com/-xEUsn7hxDMo/WFMZfObk8EI/AAAAAAAAEho/2hLXO0xUOVUYorc22jED3FsIzvghnhEVgCLcB/s1600/Czv9xzCWIAE-W1B.jpg|title=Letter from Brigadier Mead|publisher=1st Artillery Brigade and Headquarters South West|accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"mead2\">{{cite web|url=https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/15492571_1338253552859669_4065325510072663045_n.jpg?oh=aec9617d2b8b8b163d0421a7f28ed84b&oe=58F15783 |title=Letter from Brigadier Mead Part 2 |publisher=1st Artillery Brigade and Headquarters South West |accessdate=19 December 2016 }}{{dead lin